Professor Sethna is a very tough grader and expects a lot from her students. The class material is not recorded and there are no visual power points therefore it is hard to grasp all the information. The readings are very long and intricate. Good luck.

She doesn't record classes or post lecture slides, you only get notes summarized by students that aren't always posted. If you don't go to class you won't know a lot of what's going to be on the tests because she talks A LOT during lectures. Her feedback on assignments is pretty useless and doesn't actually help you improve on your written work.

the worst professor I've ever had in my four years at uottawa. so rude and condensing, when asking for help on the midterms she questioned how I was even in fourth year and gave no guidance at all on how to get a better mark.

Prof. Sethna is AMAZING!! This was probably the most interesting course I've ever taken and she made it super enjoyable! She always goes over the readings in class and has a few assignments which are challenging, but super interesting. Highly highly recommend!

She is a super difficult marker when it comes to midterms and finals. I had her for an online class and the feed back she provided for midterms and assignments wasnt even helpful, just plain rude. I would avoid ever taking any class with her. And if its mandatory, take it with another prof. You can go to class and study but still fail exams.

Was a business (HR) major but easily my fave course of my degree. Her approach to discussions on the diversities of women used an in-depth analysis of historic events. Very interesting and thought-provoking. No electronics  handwritten notes  you will focus. Must do readings to participate in discussion. Exams force you to be analytical.

So much information is covered on the tests that its difficult to study for them. there are so many readings. I went into her office hours to see how I could do better and she's very sharp, but not unfriendly.

Prof. Sethna is very clear about her expectations for this class- if you don't show up or do any of the readings, you will not do well. People act like these are unreasonable expectations but they really aren't. She's an engaging lecturer and the content was interesting. She is a historian, so make sure to know your names and dates for her exams.

Honestly don't even know why she has a 3 out of 5 .. Worst professor i've ever had , class attendance is absolutely mandatory.. oh and I should mention that she doesn't allow laptops or phones in her class and will call you out like a elementary school teacher if she sees you on your phone. TERRIBLE class .AVOID AVOID AVOID

rComments: The class content is interesting but she can be pretty rude to students, which makes it difficult to want to speak up (snarky comments, sarcasm, cutting people off, etc.) She has passion for her work but is hard to like and enjoy.

Dr. Sethna is knowledgeable in her field, but her rude comments in class make it not worth it. Makes sarcastic comments and comes off a bit elitist. Very lecture heavy, no laptops allowed. The notes are not posted online so make sure to attend class. Overall the class material is interesting, but could be taught better.

she's just... a no. I like the course but she was so unlikeable that she made it hard for you to appreciate the course. if you're expecting an easy grade, skip this class because she wants specific answers on the exams that we barely went over in class and the smallest details in the readings.

Will interrupt a student if she disagrees with them. You dont have to do the readings if you attend class because she will go over them extensively. Exams are okay but she will dock marks if you dont give her the exact answer she is looking for. Expects you to have everything memorized.

This prof was good but super tough. You won't pass if you don't do the readings and attend the lectures. Her exams were difficult because she has high expectations from everybody. She's smart and passionate about the class material which made for interesting lectures, I learned a lot. Even if I just passed this class, I recommend it to all.
Be ready for your GPA to drop. Hardest test ever, never missed a class, did all the reading and I can't even get a B....

No final exam which was great. Seminar class worth 20% participation. HEAVY reading- if you don't keep up you won't do well. Very unclear about expectations for midterm. No laptops. Would not recommend although she grades fairly

Professor Sethna is an extremely intelligent and articulate person, and she expects the same from her students. She  is tough, but in a great way that allows you to develop critical skills you'll need to have throughout your undergrad. She is extremely helpful if you ask for it and the content of her courses is super interesting. Highly recommend!

To be fair, I barely went to this class all semester & still did alright - but the classes I did go to were informative, broke my hand from writing so much, and had me actively trying not to roll my eyes at all the very arrogant remarks she made. One of those profs that teaches their opinion - strongly. No laptops/phones was unfortunate. Easy tests

Get ready to write. Sethna bans all electronic devices in her classroom. She is arrogant and likes to make fun of dumb answers, however I found her to be very knowledgeable and the subject matter of the course is interesting.  Her exams are based on what she emphasizes in class AND the readings. Memorize memorize memorize!!

Do not expect a good grade. HSS2121 is made up of mostly HSS students with science backgrounds, her whole course seemed to intend on proving that Social Sciences are better. She emphasizes the importance of critical thinking over grades but then tests on memorization solely for the midterms. The final was fair but did not make up for the midterms.

I am in no sense being bias. I got an A- in this class and let me tell you, its an extremely interesting course and she is an amazing lecturer, but you literally have you take notes from the each chapter and make sure you try and pick out whatever names  you think are important and make sure its spelled clearly on the exam. Goodluck!

The course and readings (there are a lot) are very interesting! I'm a social science student with an interest in health so I took this course for fun and got a lot out of it. Be warned: her tests are  difficult - be prepared to memorize meticulous details from the text  course pack. There is a no laptop policy. Great speaker but a bit demeaning.

She's a great lecturer, but they way she speaks can be demeaning at times. She tells us that we should be reading more books, although we already have a whole textbook and a course-pack that we need to read through. Her final also had multiple mistakes in it, but make sure you memorize names, and don't make any spelling mistakes.

Sethna is probably the most interesting lecturer I have ever had at uOttawa. However, she emphasizes on critical thinking throughout the course but there's absolutely NO critical thinking in her exams. Learn names (all of them from the book), dates and examples BY HEART (this isn't critical thinking at all its memorizing).

HSS2121 Winter session 2015 was ABSOLUTELY AWFUL. This is the worst professor I have ever had. Spends her lectures emphasizing about material and showing videos that are not tested on. Derives all her questions from textbook, but does not touch on it in class. Seriously needs to adjust to the 21st century. Exams are all short answer.
Her mid terms have questions I don't remember learning in class or in the lecture. Was told it would be an easy A, I think I have a C in the class.

She's a good lecturer that makes the course interesting. She plays plenty of movies during class and regularly dismisses students early.  Where she really fails are the tests. Memorize, memorize and do more memorization and you'll be fine.  Despite what she claims, there is absolutely no critical thinking needed in this course.

A nice change to the typical university course. Sethna drives the class to focus on comprehension instead of memorization. She uses different media to reinforce the message. I've never taken a history class but i am  really enjoying it. The three hour class goes by faster than my hour twenty classes!

Amazing lecturer, one of the few I've had where my mind never wandered throughout the lecture. She is not a fan of electronics in the class and will give you one warning for using your cell phone before you get to sing a Bieber song in front of everyone. If a laptop is better for taking notes on though you can talk to her and she'll let you though.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Dr Sethna is truly one of a kind. She is very knowledgeable, enthusiastic, and engaging. The textbook was also very interesting. However she is quite stubborn and often times focused on the history of medicine from a purely feministic point of view because of a personal vendetta. Exams were tough, but fair. If you're eager to learn take it with her

Amazing prof. You learn SO much SO quickly- but it's totally worth it. She expects a lot from her students, so don't take this class if you're just trying to fill your time table. Take this class and learn from her! She's excellent.

Professor Sethna did an amazing job teaching this class and conveyed the subject matter in a great way. She doesn't allow laptops, and does not post notes online, so its very important that you attend class every week. There is a lot of reading and expects you to thoroughly understand each article assigned.

Sethna did a good job of teaching this course for the first time. Be warned, there is a lot of reading to do and you are expected to participate in the seminar as well as work on your public speaking skills. Papers were confusing, her instructions not always clear. But if you ask for help she'll give it to you :)

The material for this class was really interesting and Prof Sethna did an excellent job of addressing delicate subjects in a politically correct and well-rounded way. However, I thought this would be an easy course because it has no papers, but the readings were hugely important and her exams are very tricky.

Walked into this class thinking I was going to hate it. Surprisingly it was a very interesting class thanks to her! She doesn't allow laptops. I wouldn't say it was a lot of work but the tests were very specific and you basically have to memorize the readings along with her lectures, which won't be too bad if you enjoy it anyway.

She was very clear with her notes and conveyed the topics very well using videos and pictures a lot. You MUST read the textbook and take notes on it for midterms/exams. She asks very specific questions from the book. If you do not attend class you will not pass because exams are based on her notes and she doesn't post them. Helps if you ask her.

Beware of this class. Yes, it is interesting, but a TON of work. You will spend most of your weekend trying to get through the dense coursepack readings. There are a LOT of readings. You cannot skim either, she expects you to remember every minor detail for about 15 readings. There was too much info packed into the course to be effective.

AMAZING.  She is misunderstood by those who give poor ratings. She cares quite a bit about students no matter how big the class is. She is intimidating, but if you approach her and need help she is great.Her classes are not easy however I have learned the most from her classes. She challenges her students in a way most profs don't. Fave prof by far

Although she is an excellent lecturer and makes the class interesting, her midterms are impossible to do well in. She bases the question on miniscule details in the textbook, so coming to her class and taking notes is completely useless. Whats the point of great teaching skills when none of what you teach is going to be tested on? AVOID.

The class was interesting, and the prof is good at explaining the material. It seems that the laptop ban makes the classes move at a slower pace, but really it's worth it, you're forced to pay attention and at least for me, it showed in the grade I received.

Sethna is very fair and clear with. Exams reflect class material very well. If you pay attention to the exam questions and answer merely what it is asking, not go deeper you will do well. Do the readings and keep in mind key terms and general ideas. Fill in the blanks on tests are difficult. She is super nice and her lectures are engaging. Great!
She is a great prof, her lectures are actually so interesting and it's not really that hard of a class. Great speaker

AMAZING! Not only is Prof Sethna an amazing speaker but she clarifys everything you need to know so you're fully prepd for the exams. don't get thrown off by the laptop ban (i freaked out at first too) but it really does make you do better in the class. She is insightful and makes you thinks about things, she made me love history!

An insightful teacher who encourages you to maintain a  critical eye of politics and media. Do the readings, participate in class, talk to her in office hours. Just amazing. This class and professor changed my life, no joke. Not for the lazy or weak of heart. Totally worth it in the end

Interesting course. Take good notes! She bans laptops, kinda helpful in the long run attention-wise. Read all the class readings in the coursepack! Midterm was hard, quizzes are easy as long as you read! Study hard and understand it and it'll be fine.

the course is really interesting.  I learn a lot regarding the history of racism.  Her miderm is a easy but her quiz are extremely hard. They are not related to the reading sometimes.  She ran the course like a dictator.  She banned the use of laptops in the classroom.    I will not take another course with her ever again.

Sethna is AMAZING.  She's talking about things that challenge us as a society. She's smart and she expects her students to come to class prepared.  She has high standards and she doesn't mess around.  I took another class of hers just because she taught it.

didnt participate at all in class discussions, didnt do any of the readings and still did well on midterm + paper! easy class if you pay attention and study the material which is easy to do since it was interesting. shes  smart and is a feminist but doesnt hate men. surprisingly ended up being a good class!!
Her first time teaching HSS2121. Very nice, acts like she is helpful in person. Strict with disregard for student's farewell. Avoid her teaching this class if you can.

One of my favorite profs for sure. Very interesting material and she conveys it very well. NOT a bird course, reading was very heavy and participation is expected. Getting a good mark takes lots of effort but it's well worth it.

good prof
